{
  "name": "BEN_CNTNU_PRTN_CTFN_TYP_F",
  "object_type": "TABLE",
  "description": "BEN_CNTNU_PRTN_CTFN_TYP_F identifies the certification that may be required in order to continue participating in a plan.  The certification is associated with a continuing participation eligibility  profile, which  identifies the eligibility criteria for participation in a compensation plan on a continuing basis. For example,  after a life event occurs which typically disqualifies a participant from participation and/or reduces/eliminates any employer contribution subsidy. . In the US, continuing participation is a focus for COBRA, in and outside the US, plan sponsors may allow prior participants in a  plan (typically medical) to continue to participate if that person pays  the premiums.",
  "schema": "FUSION",
  "owner": "BEN",
